Package: IRTsimrel
Title: Reliability-Targeted Simulation for Item Response Data
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("JoonHo", "Lee", 
           email = "jlee296@ua.edu", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0006-4019-8703"))
Description: Provides tools for reliability-targeted simulation studies in 
    Item Response Theory (IRT). Implements two calibration algorithms: 
    Empirical Quadrature Calibration (EQC) for fast deterministic calibration, 
    and Stochastic Approximation Calibration (SPC/SAC) for validation and 
    complex data-generating processes. Functions are provided for generating 
    latent ability distributions with various shapes (normal, bimodal, skewed, 
    heavy-tailed, etc.), simulating realistic item parameters using the Item 
    Response Warehouse (IRW), and validating calibration results using the 
    TAM package.
